Climate Report

Temperature and Precipitation 1960-2014

Joseph Wu

2018-11-16

Data

I use a data called temp_prec_middle_encrypted from University of Delaware to plot temperature and precipitation maps for North America, for June month 1960 (first year in the data), 1986 (in the middle of the observation period), and 2014 (the last year)

Temperature

The temperture seems getting higher the lower the latitude gets. The pattern looks resonable and I dont see any major difference between these years.

Precipitation

Theres more precipitation in the Southeast of North America and Northeast of North America. The pattern seems reasonable and it seems like the precipitation is increasing between these years.

Note:

you cannot do any conclusions about long-term trend based on just 3 figures. If you are interested, you are welcome to explore long-term trends in these data, but be sure to use more suitable methods.
